      "tags": [
        "HITL"
      ],
      "audience": "public",
      "description": "Submit a HITL request and optionally register a completion callback.\n\nThis endpoint forwards the request payload to the internal HITL service,\nwhich evaluates WHEN/WHO/WHAT/WHERE and either:\n- returns immediately with `status=no-hitl`, or\n- accepts the request and waits for human/auto completion.\n\nRequest JSON (fields commonly used by callers):\n{\n  \"caller_id\": \"<instance-or-activity-id>\",\n  \"instance_id\": \"<optional alias of caller_id>\",\n  \"org_id\": \"<optional; inferred from session/api key when available>\",\n  \"agent_name\": \"<optional>\",\n  \"hitl\": {\n    \"enable\": true,\n    \"when\": \"<condition|always>\",\n    \"who\": \"<initiator|email>\",\n    \"what\": \"approval|notify\",\n    \"where\": \"amp|email\"\n  },\n  \"callback\": {\n    \"url\": \"https://caller.example.com/hitl/callback\",\n    \"secret\": \"<optional shared secret>\",\n    \"timeout_ms\": 5000\n  }\n}\n\nCallback payload on completion (single attempt, best effort):\n{\n  \"caller_id\": \"<id>\",\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"resolution\": \"approve|reject|modify|defer|unknown\",\n  \"method\": \"human|auto\",\n  \"workitem_id\": \"<id_or_empty>\",\n  \"information\": \"<optional detail>\",\n  \"event_ts\": \"<ISO-8601 UTC timestamp>\"\n}"
    },
